<item>
            <title>[SPARK-3807] SparkSql does not work for tables created using custom serde</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-3807</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;SparkSql crashes on selecting tables using custom serde. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Example:&lt;br/&gt;
----------------&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;CREATE EXTERNAL TABLE table_name PARTITIONED BY ( a int) ROW FORMAT &apos;SERDE &quot;org.apache.hadoop.hive.serde2.thrift.ThriftDeserializer&quot; with serdeproperties(&quot;serialization.format&quot;=&quot;org.apache.thrift.protocol.TBinaryProtocol&quot;,&quot;serialization.class&quot;=&quot;ser_class&quot;) STORED AS SEQUENCEFILE;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The following exception is seen on running a query like &apos;select * from table_name limit 1&apos;: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ERROR CliDriver: org.apache.hadoop.hive.serde2.SerDeException: java.lang.NullPointerException &lt;br/&gt;
